<hr>

<h2 id="what">What is 4taba?</h2>
Above all a place to have fun.<br>
Prounounced "Shitaba", it is an imageboard for discussing various hobbyist topics, modelled after Japanese style discussion and imageboards such as 2channel and Futaba, and English imageboards such as 4chan.<br>
<br>
The source code for the site can be found <a href="https://github.com/4taba/4taba">here</a>. Feel free to use it however you wish. If you do use it please send me an email as I'd love to hear about your project.
<br>
<h2 id="trip">Why are there no tripcodes?</h2>
This is because the function of tripcodes can be accomplished without the feature being built directly into the site.<br>
If there is a need for a poster to be identified there are other means available to them such as encrypted signatures. This also has the benefit of dircouraging excessive casual use of identification.<br>
<br>
<h2 id="mixed">What is a mixed board view?</h2>
You can view multiple boards at the same time for your convenience. Just use the plus sign to join them like so:<br>
<a href="/a+ni">&gt;&gt;&gt;/a+ni/</a><br>
The first board is considered to be the main one, so if you post a thread it will go there.
<br>
Additionally boards may be subtracted (which is really only useful on the /all/ board) like so:<br>
<a href="/all-ho">&gt;&gt;&gt;/all-ho/</a><br>
<br>
<h2 id="boards">What are unlisted boards?</h2>
An feature to give flexibility to the board list.<br>
<br>
These are <em>not</em> user created/owned boards. Users can't give them a title or control them any differently from the main boards.<br>
Unlisted boards may be purged and/or repurposed at any time. For more stability please use the main boards.<br>
<br>
To use, simply modify the URL to point to the board label of your choice (e.g. <a href="/test">&gt;&gt;&gt;/test/</a>) and start posting.<br>
<br>
<h2 id="bb">How do I format my post?</h2>
You can use the following BBCodes:<br>
<ul>
<li>[code] - Create a monospace code block.</li>
<li>[ja] - Set text size and font for Shift_JIS art.</li>
<li>[spoiler] - Spoiler text.</li>
</ul><br>
